*There is progress in evaluating the ecological, socio-economic and governance effectiveness of South Africa’s Marine Protected Areas (MPAs). Advances in ecological effectiveness are evident but there are gaps in participation, ecosystem representation, connectivity and governance. Diversified conservation measures can help address gaps and provide new opportunities to safeguard both biodiversity and cultural heritage. Increasing extent of protection alone is not enough to advance marine ecosystems to Well Protected, the condition of marine ecosystems in conservation areas also needs to be improved. South Africa needs to better include people in the design, implementation and co-management of conservation areas.*

![Fisherwoman in the iSimangaliso MPA and World Heritage Site © Kerry Sink](imgs/Blackrock_oct13_1_328.png)

